  "doc_id": "prion_0788",
  "text": "We report the case of a 76 year old woman who presented with a clinical picture initially typical of a vascular dementia.\nThe diagnosis was revised to Creutzfeldt-Jacob Disease in the terminal stages.\nWhile Creutzfeldt-Jacob Disease is rare, one must consider it in the differential diagnosis as it can mimic other dementias particularly in the chronic form which we describe here.",
